---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Editorial Policy - Baijiu365';
const description = 'How Baijiu365 writes, reviews, and updates baijiu guidance for global readers.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <header class="article-header"><div class="narrow"><p class="eyebrow">Trust</p><h1>Editorial Policy</h1><p class="lede">Baijiu365 is built as a practical field guide, not a bottle sales page.</p></div></header>
  <section class="content"><article>
    <div class="decision-box">
      <h2>Short version</h2>
      <p>We prioritize useful guidance, clear limits, and reader safety over hype. When a claim needs market verification or hands-on tasting evidence, we say so instead of pretending certainty.</p>
    </div>
    <h2>How We Decide What To Publish</h2>
    <p>Articles are chosen around real reader decisions: learning baijiu basics, comparing aroma types, choosing a first bottle, avoiding fake or risky purchases, serving baijiu with food, and understanding brand context.</p>
    <h2>Review Standards</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Guides should answer the reader's main question near the top.</li>
      <li>Buying advice should separate taste, occasion, budget, and authenticity risk.</li>
      <li>Tasting language should be descriptive rather than absolute.</li>
      <li>We avoid unverifiable prestige claims, fake vintage certainty, and pressure to buy.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>If a factual issue is found, we update the article and, when meaningful, note the change in the development log or related planning docs.</p>
    <div class="next-links">
      <a href="/about/">About Baijiu365</a>
      <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>
    </div>
  </article></section>
</BaseLayout>
